# Rules Template

gamet-init generates these based on tech stack detection:

## For Next.js / React projects:
```yaml
---
paths:
  - "app/**"
  - "components/**"
---
# Framework Conventions
- [Generated from tech-advisor scan or Q7 answers]
```

## For database-heavy projects:
```yaml
---
paths:
  - "prisma/**"
  - "lib/services/**"
  - "app/api/**"
---
# Database Conventions
- [Generated from tech-advisor scan or Q7 answers]
```

## For Python projects:
```yaml
---
paths:
  - "**/*.py"
---
# Python Conventions
- [Generated from tech-advisor scan]
```

## Universal rules (always generated):
```yaml
---
# No paths — loads always
---
# GAMET Development Rules
- Every new feature should start with impact analysis (gamet-impact)
- Use GAMET panel for review before shipping
- Update learning log after each review
- Epistemic discipline: VERIFIED vs ASSUMED vs UNCERTAIN
```
